Class PatternMatchingCommandGenerator

java.lang.Object
  hjb.http.cmd.PatternMatchingCommandGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
JMSCommandGenerator
Direct Known Subclasses:
CommitSessionGenerator, CreateBrowserGenerator, CreateConnectionGenerator, CreateConsumerGenerator, CreateProducerGenerator, CreateSessionGenerator, CreateSubscriberGenerator, DeleteConnectionFactoryGenerator, DeleteConnectionGenerator, DeleteDestinationGenerator, DeleteProviderGenerator, DeleteSessionGenerator, ReadMetaDataGenerator, ReceiveFromConsumerGenerator, ReceiveFromSubscriberGenerator, RegisterConnectionFactoryGenerator, RegisterDestinationGenerator, RegisterProviderGenerator, RollbackSessionGenerator, SendHJBMessageGenerator, StartConnectionGenerator, StopConnectionGenerator, ViewQueueGenerator
public abstract class PatternMatchingCommandGenerator
extends Object
implements JMSCommandGenerator

PatternMatchingCommandGenerator is a base class for JMSCommandGenerator implementations that should be invoked on specific paths in the HJBServlet that match a particuler Pattern.

It implements generateCommand(HttpServletRequest, HJBRoot) as a Template Method, and defines two abstract methods getPathPattern() and constructCommandFrom(HttpServletRequest, HJBRoot) that subclasses implement to produce their required behaviour.

By default, the value of HJBRoot.getCommandRunner() is returned as the value of getAssignedCommandRunner(). Subclasses can change this when they implement constructCommandFrom(HttpServletRequest, HJBRoot). Should this be done, the method useRootCommandRunner() should also be overridden to return false

Author:
Tim Emiola
